Scenarios

We apply the extended Social MDP framework to a multi-agent gridworld which consists of two agents (a yellow robot and red robot), two physical landmarks (a construction site and a tree) and three objects (an axe, wooden log, and a water bucket). Physical goals consist of moving the desired objects to one of the landmarks. Agents can have no social goal or one of the five social goals: cooperation, conflict, competition, coercion, or exchange leading to 2x6x6 = 72 scenarios.
